channel.title: Computer trying to shut it self off?
channel.description: So, my piece of shit windows 7 is constantly trying to shut it self down, not like the PSU is going out, like windows tries to go through the log off process, by closing all my programs. Its quite annoying because it happens the most while I'm playing a game or something. I've scanned with the following programs ever since the issue started: Spybot S&D, Norton, Zone alarm, Malawarebytes, and super anti-spy. Nothing finds any malicious software, when I do a google search, its full of people who have blown PSU's, which isn't my case, its really upsetting and I can't do a system restore because I don't have the disc, and until I can save up $100 to buy a new disc, I have to find a temporary fix.

item.title: Computer trying to shut it self off?
item.dc:creator: @Loveandpower Loveandpower
item.description:
@Loveandpower wrote:

Go to Start Menu Type gpedit.msc
Go for the following option:
User Configuration\Administrative Templates\Start Menu and Taskbar
Double click on Remove and Prevent Access to the Shut Down command
Select any one of the option “Not configured” or “Disabled”
Shut Down the Group Policy window.
Might need to reboot

And if this doesn’t work…

go here: http://social.technet.microsoft.com/Forums/en/ITCG/threads/ and ask the really smart scripters there.
